data.description: Stylishly updated in 2021, this classic Tampa home on a large .26 acre fenced corner lot offers the rare combination of location convenience and affordability.  Covered carport parking and extended driveway allow for multiple vehicle and/or recreational vehicle parking.  The front entry brings you into the open main living space and dining nook combination that fills with natural light through the triple-slider glass doors and ample windows.  The kitchen offers granite countertops, stainless appliances, and lots of white shaker-style cabinets.  Two of the bedrooms are about the same size, and the smaller third bedroom has a pet door installed to allow for pets to access the fenced yard area.  The bathroom includes a shower/tub combo and has been updated with new tile, flooring, vanity, and fixtures.  The laundry room is detached and can be accessed via the kitchen door and covered carport, washer and dryer stay with the home.  This home requires no HOA and no CDD.  The roof and stainless kitchen appliances were installed 2021, electrical wiring and panels were updated 2021, AC system 2017, water heater 2010.  The property used to have a utilities easement behind it, so the south fenceline is currently apx 5' inside the property line.  A survey is available.  Just outside of the action, but very near downtown Tampa, Ybor City, MacDill AFB, sports and entertainment arenas, and with nearby access to Interstate 4 and Interstate 75, toll roads, and other major roadways, this home is in the heart of all that Tampa has to offer!  Come see your new home!
